Author: Codex <codex@local>
Date:   Thu Jun 4 18:57:36 2026 +0000

    Switch cookie pool from Firefox SQLite to Netscape cookies.txt
    
    YouTube rotates auth tokens (PSIDTS) on every open browser tab as
    anti-abuse. The old --cookies-from-browser model caused race conditions
    between Firefox and yt-dlp, and the cookie_refresher background task was
    actively counterproductive (open tab → token rotation → stale cookies).
    
    New model:
    - cookie_profiles/<name>.txt holds one Netscape cookies.txt per account
    - yt-dlp uses --cookies <path> as both input and output (writes back
      Set-Cookie updates on every run, so cookies stay fresh through use)
    - Pool scans the directory at startup; ID = filename without .txt
    - No browser ever opens the account again after initial export
    
    Removed:
    - cookie_refresher module (no longer needed, was counterproductive)
    - Firefox profile discovery (profiles.ini, materialize_profiles_cache)
    - profile_dir / source_profile_dir / cookies_sqlite fields
    - files/youtube_links.txt
    
    Migration: each account must be re-exported via the procedure in
    cookie_profiles/README.md (incognito → login → robots.txt → export → close).
    Long-lived auth cookies last months as long as the profile is never opened
    in a browser again.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

