[32m+[m[32m### Why cookies.txt instead of Firefox profiles[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mYouTube rotates auth tokens (`__Secure-1PSIDTS`, `__Secure-3PSIDTS`) on every[m
[32m+[m[32mopen YouTube browser tab as anti-abuse. The previous architecture (Firefox[m
[32m+[m[32m`--cookies-from-browser`) caused race conditions: Firefox would rotate tokens[m
[32m+[m[32mon disk while yt-dlp was reading them, and any background "keep-alive" of the[m
[32m+[m[32mprofile made things worse, not better.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe cookies.txt model has a single owner (yt-dlp), no race conditions, and the[m
[32m+[m[32mlong-lived auth cookies (`SID`, `__Secure-3PSID`) stay valid for months as long[m
[32m+[m[32mas the account is never opened in a browser again.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Account setup (one-time, manual)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSee `cookie_profiles/README.md` for the full procedure. Summary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Private/incognito Firefox window → log in to YouTube[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Navigate to `youtube.com/robots.txt` (avoid activity on home/feed)[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Export `youtube.com` cookies with "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" extension[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Save to `cookie_profiles/<name>.txt`[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Close window, never open that account in a browser again[m
