[32m+[m[32m# cookie_profiles/[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEach `*.txt` file in this directory is one YouTube account, in Netscape[m
[32m+[m[32mcookies.txt format. The filename (without `.txt`) becomes the cookie ID[m
[32m+[m[32mshown in the pool (`account1.txt` → `account1`).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How to set up a new account[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe goal is to capture a fresh logged-in session **once**, then never[m
[32m+[m[32mopen that account in a browser again. yt-dlp will keep the cookies alive[m
[32m+[m[32mthrough normal use (it writes back `Set-Cookie` updates after every run).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhy this matters: YouTube rotates auth tokens (`__Secure-3PSIDTS`, etc.)[m
[32m+[m[32mon every open YouTube tab as anti-abuse. If you open the same account in[m
[32m+[m[32ma browser later, the tokens get rotated and the yt-dlp cookies become[m
[32m+[m[32mstale. So: log in → export → close → never open again.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Steps[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Open a **private/incognito** Firefox window (Ctrl+Shift+P).[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Log in to YouTube with the account.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Navigate the tab to <https://www.youtube.com/robots.txt> (a static[m
[32m+[m[32m   page that does not trigger session activity). **Do not** stay on the[m
[32m+[m[32m   homepage or feed.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Use the browser extension **"Get cookies.txt LOCALLY"** to export the[m
[32m+[m[32m   `youtube.com` cookies as Netscape format.[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Save the file to `cookie_profiles/<account_name>.txt` on the server.[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Close the private window without ever opening YouTube there again.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Validation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAfter dropping a file in here, restart the bot:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32msystemctl restart abc[m
[32m+[m[32mjournalctl -u abc -n 30 | grep -i cookie[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe startup log will show how many profiles were discovered.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When cookies expire[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf a profile starts failing (yt-dlp returns "Sign in to confirm…" or[m
[32m+[m[32msimilar), it will be marked as a bad cookie and excluded from the pool.[m
[32m+[m[32mRe-do the setup procedure above to replace the file. The long-lived[m
[32m+[m[32mauth cookies (`SID`, `__Secure-3PSID`) typically last months as long as[m
[32m+[m[32mthey are not touched by a browser.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Notes[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Maximum 20 accounts in the pool (`DEFAULT_MAX_COOKIES`).[m
[32m+[m[32m- Files are sorted by filename alphabetically.[m
[32m+[m[32m- The pool uses random selection (excluding the last-used cookie and any[m
[32m+[m[32m  on cooldown).[m
[32m+[m[32m- 429s put a cookie on 20-hour cooldown (`/cookie_429` legacy command,[m
[32m+[m[32m  or automatic via the YouTube handler).[m
